{
  "texts": [
    "Fine-tuning BERT with multi-loss functions: Yang et al. (2020) proposed R2BERT, a framework that leverages BERT for essay representation and incorporates multi-loss methods, including regression loss and ranking loss, to optimize the learning process.",
    "This study viewed AES task as both a regression and ranking problem.",
    "The rationale behind this approach is that assigning grades and rankings are complementary tasks in real-world exam evaluation scenarios.",
    "As it is shown in Fig. 6, R2BERT employs BERT for essay representation, and then applies fully connected linear layer followed by sigmoid function on the fixed essay representation, [CLS].",
    "After predicting the score, both the accuracy and rank information are utilized to optimize the learning process."
  ]
}